	   <tr><td colspan=2>I was a bit forceful because you've got some wrong information, bud.&nbsp;&nbsp;Test after test has shown:<br><br>1) Agility does NOT affect your dodge/parry/riposte.  The game designers even confirmed this.<br><br>2) Strength does NOT affect your damage done by much- no more than a few points per minute per 10 points of strength.  Considering that with a decent weapon you could be doing 500 points per minute, having that extra 50 strength to do an extra  2% more damage just doesn't make sense.<br><br>3) Dexterity does NOT affect your hit rate.  The game designers confirmed this too.<br><br>Armor Class, however, DOES significantly affect your performance.  Bunches of tests have pegged adding 1 armor class as adding at LEAST 10hp to your survival in combat.  Thus, going from 700ac to 900ac adds about 2000hp to your survival.  In other words, a fighter with 700ac and 3000hp will die at about the same time as a fighter with 900ac and 1000hp.  Pretty big effect, no??  Like I said before, read the the sites and the guides, look at the evidence,  and decide for yourself.<br>&nbsp;<br>Puggins Fizzlefoot<br>Personal Footgroomer for Fizzlethorpe Bristlebane, Bless his hairy little toes<br></td></tr>
